<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by NightStalkerX6 on 04-26-2001 07:37 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">D23: "I have never reported anyone, but I can give you a real good reason.
Minding my own business, someone either acts like an ass over shout or ooc (no, that would NEVER happen?) or they are directly making the game less enjoyable to me (training my group, spamming us with stupid shit, repeatedly begging for buffs, items, cash...) Basically, anyone being an ass. I'm not talking about me seeing someone in lvl 50 gear that is lvl 1, not my business and I don't care. Hell, I make it a point to NEVER /con a player unless I am grouping up with them. And even then, it is none of my business what they have for gear. I don't think I have inspected someone (except trying to beat the ninja-looting necro I group with, lil bastard!) Sorry, rambling..

Be an ass to me and I see you doing something later on that might get you in trouble, well, since it is not really possible for me to slap ya in the face, and who knows, it might get my ass beat, Yep, you guessed it, I just might be inclined to /report you or /petition you."

- okay, this is totally different from what we're talking about. Some person following you around for 10 minutes, /poke-ing you, begging for SoW, clarity, rez, whatever and hiting the monster your fighting is not even closely related with a person stading ontop of a large rock at 3:30am blasting creatures that can't hit them..that's the whole point this DOESN'T MAKE THE GAME LESS ENJOYABLE FOR YOU, it makes the game MORE enjoyable for the person, who obviously likes to do that. If you don't cheat, than don't cheat..that's all there is to it, i respect that, gain your levels however you want, but why let the jealousy get to you enough where your going to report someone because he's doing something you don't "want" to do. I mean really. Now i'm all for reporting someone that's screwing you up while your playing, cuz like you said you can't slap someone in the game (unfortuantly), but unless the guy who is "cheating" is draining his mana from a rock at the spawn site your camping, how is he effecting you in any way? just let him be, and mind your own business. 


